{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014kSQWcTShhnr6UA9oSzkGS","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→export type UserRating = {\n     2→  id?: number;\n     3→  mediaItemId: number;\n     4→  date: number;\n     5→  userId: number;\n     6→  rating?: number;\n     7→  review?: string;\n     8→  episodeId?: number;\n     9→  seasonId?: number;\n    10→};\n    11→\n    12→export const userRatingColumns = <const>[\n    13→  'id',\n    14→  'date',\n    15→  'mediaItemId',\n    16→  'userId',\n    17→  'rating',\n    18→  'review',\n    19→  'episodeId',\n    20→  'seasonId',\n    21→];\n    22→\n    23→export class UserRatingFilters {\n    24→  public static mediaItemUserRating = (rating: UserRating) => {\n    25→    return !rating.seasonId && !rating.episodeId;\n    26→  };\n    27→\n    28→  public static seasonUserRating = (rating: UserRating) => {\n    29→    return Boolean(rating.seasonId && !rating.episodeId);\n    30→  };\n    31→\n    32→  public static episodeUserRating = (rating: UserRating) => {\n    33→    return Boolean(rating.episodeId);\n    34→  };\n    35→}\n    36→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012Qfg38rYA2YRJuYDHpyGvR","session_id":"c055fa73-cbc8-4bb7-a5e6-009e4e9c5990","uuid":"8fc13519-c59a-4ff3-ab12-02a42d722bd8"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017zxc76C54ddwuYnWouknTL","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→export type Progress = {\n     2→  id?: number;\n     3→  date: number;\n     4→  mediaItemId: number;\n     5→  episodeId?: number;\n     6→  userId: number;\n     7→  progress?: number;\n     8→  duration?: number;\n     9→  action?: 'playing' | 'paused';\n    10→  device?: string;\n    11→};\n    12→\n    13→export const progressColumns = <const>[\n    14→  'id',\n    15→  'date',\n    16→  'mediaItemId',\n    17→  'episodeId',\n    18→  'userId',\n    19→  'duration',\n    20→  'progress',\n    21→  'action',\n    22→  'device',\n    23→];\n    24→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012Qfg38rYA2YRJuYDHpyGvR","session_id":"c055fa73-cbc8-4bb7-a5e6-009e4e9c5990","uuid":"c7364135-2727-45d3-be7a-1860d208e558"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WfRHcjzxGZdZdE8WPKCTW1","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→export type Seen = {\n     2→  id?: number;\n     3→  date?: number;\n     4→  mediaItemId: number;\n     5→  episodeId?: number;\n     6→  userId: number;\n     7→  duration?: number;\n     8→};\n     9→\n    10→export const seenColumns = <const>[\n    11→  'date',\n    12→  'id',\n    13→  'mediaItemId',\n    14→  'episodeId',\n    15→  'userId',\n    16→  'duration',\n    17→];\n    18→\n    19→export class SeenFilters {\n    20→  public static mediaItemSeenValue = (seen: Seen) => {\n    21→    return Boolean(!seen.episodeId);\n    22→  };\n    23→\n    24→  public static episodeSeenValue = (seen: Seen) => {\n    25→    return Boolean(seen.episodeId);\n    26→  };\n    27→}\n    28→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012Qfg38rYA2YRJuYDHpyGvR","session_id":"c055fa73-cbc8-4bb7-a5e6-009e4e9c5990","uuid":"eb18ddd4-633b-47ea-8165-043be06eb432"}
